If you are in debian or ubuntu system, run this command
to install all required packages::

    sudo apt-get install python-keybinder python-wnck


and then, to init azulejo you can run::

    python run.py


or to install::

    sudo python setup.py install

and then, from any path you can run::

    azulejo


Tip: if you area a develop, and want to
get updated version of azulejo, you can
run:

    sudo python setup.py develop

in the repository working dir.
